% You are an expert TypeScript/Next.js engineer. Implement the composition preview API route.

% Role & Scope
  This module implements GET /api/pipeline/compositions/preview — renders a Remotion still frame for a named component and serves it as a PNG. Supports both on-demand rendering and cached raw image serving.

% Requirements
  1) Endpoint: GET /api/pipeline/compositions/preview?component=<name>[&section=<id>][&raw=1]
  2) Return 400 if component query param is missing
  3) Check getCompositionArtifactState() — return 409 with { error, stale: true } if stale
  4) raw=1 mode: serve cached PNG from outputs/previews/ as image/png with Content-Length and Cache-Control: public, max-age=60. Stream via Readable.toWeb(). Return 404 if file doesn't exist
  5) Render mode: resolve componentName → Remotion compositionId, call renderStill(compositionId, FPS, pngPath) where FPS=30, return JSON { url, specPath, specContent }
  6) The url field points back to this endpoint with raw=1 and the same component/section params
  7) On render failure, return 500 with { error, specPath, specContent }
  8) When compositionId can't be resolved, return 404 with { error, specPath, specContent } (specPath from fallback section lookup)

% Composition ID Resolution (resolvePreviewTarget)
  Given componentName and optional sectionId, scan project.json sections (filtered by sectionId if provided):
  1) Use resolveSectionCompositionIds(section) to get the composition list for each section
  2) Check if section-scoped name ({sectionId}_{componentName}) is in the list
  3) Check if componentName is already in the list as-is
  4) Fallback: {sectionId}_main → section.compositionId
  5) Wrapper names ({compositionId}Wrapper or {sectionId}Wrapper) → section.compositionId
  6) Only when comps.length === 0 (no registered graph): check on-disk artifacts via componentArtifactExists

% Remotion ID Mapping (compToRemotionId)
  Convert resolved name to Remotion composition ID: toPascalCase → kebab-case.
  If PascalCase starts with a digit, prefix with toPascalCase(sectionId) before converting to kebab.

% On-Disk Artifact Lookup (componentArtifactExists)
  Check these candidate paths in order under getAppRemotionSrcDir():
  1) {sectionId}_{componentName}.tsx (scoped flat file)
  2) {componentName}.tsx (unscoped flat file)
  3) For NN_ prefixed names: {NN}-{StrippedPascal}/index.ts and {SectionPascal}{NN}{StrippedPascal}/index.ts
  4) For non-prefixed: {PascalCase}/index.ts (directory component)
  Return first match with its resolvedId and compositionId.

% Spec Resolution (resolvePreviewSpec)
  Look for matching .md file in specs/{section.specDir}/:
  - {componentName}.md
  - Strip section prefix: {componentName without sectionId_}.md
  - For _main/wrapper components: spec.md

% Preview Filename
  Cache-safe: outputs/previews/{sectionId}--{componentName}.png (or just {componentName}.png without section).

% Dependencies
  - @/lib/project: loadProject (returns project config with sections array)
  - @/lib/render: renderStill(compositionId, frame, outputPath)
  - @/lib/projects: getAppRemotionSrcDir(), getProjectDir()
  - @/app/api/pipeline/_lib/composition-manifest: getCompositionArtifactState(), resolveSectionCompositionIds()

% Instructions
  - Use fs and path for file operations, stream.Readable for raw serving
  - Use NextResponse for JSON responses, plain NextResponse constructor for streaming
  - Export only the GET handler
  - PreviewSection type: { id, compositionId, specDir?, compositions? }
  - toPascalCase helper: replace (^|_)(\w) with uppercase
